Source: compsync
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Miguel Rodo <miguel.rodo@uct.ac.za>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 10)
Standards-Version: 4.5.1
Homepage: https://github.com/MiguelRodo/compsync

Package: compsync
Architecture: all
Depends: bash, git, python3
Description: Synchronize DevContainer configurations from MiguelRodo/comp
 compsync is an interactive CLI tool that clones the MiguelRodo/comp
 repository and applies its "gold standard" DevContainer configurations
 to your current project, including:
  - .devcontainer/Dockerfile
  - .devcontainer/devcontainer.json (with deep JSON merge support)
  - .devcontainer/prebuild/devcontainer.json
  - .devcontainer/renv/ (R environment lockfile)
  - .devcontainer/scripts/ (R utility scripts)
  - .devcontainer/.Rprofile (overwrite or append)
  - scripts/ (Bash utilities with automatic +x permissions)
 .
 Designed for R/Python data-science projects using VS Code DevContainers.
